TEXT(beginproblem());
BEGIN_TEXT
Find the particular solution of the differential equation
\[\frac{x^2}{y^2-$aa}\frac{dy}{dx} = \frac{1}{2y}\]
satisfying the initial condition \(y(1)=\sqrt{$bb}\).
$BR
Answer: \(y=\)  \{ ans_rule(45)\}.
$BR
Your answer should be a function of \(x\).
END_TEXT

